    {
        "client_msg_id": "4acbec19-5d97-402a-803d-338b74110df3",
        "type": "message",
        "text": "Threads are unneeded complexity--they actually get in the way--for real time chat, exchanging timely information. Eg, coordinating the virtual symposium that just ended, over in <#CJT25RWKE|research-center>. For this use case, archiving old posts is not important.\n\nThreads are useful for intellectual discussions, where you might want to go back and review a discussion from 6 months ago, without having to filter out all of the other unrelated chatter that happened at the same time the discussion was taking place.\n\nSince our motivation for replacing Slack is that we need full historical access to the archive, it follows that the replacement needs to support threads. A corollary is that the Matrix integration should only be used for reading the forum, or for real-time chat. Please use the threaded interface to participate in intellectual discussions.",
        "user": "UJN1TAYEQ",
        "ts": "1574360996.028600",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_profile": {
